.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-image_tool \- Resize, convert formats, strip EXIF metadata, optimize file size, and
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility image_tool
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Resize, convert formats, strip EXIF metadata, optimize file size, and
.SH BACKENDS
.PP
Subcommand   |   Required tool   |   Package
info, resize, convert, strip, thumb   |   \fCconvert\fP/\fCmagick\fP   |   ImageMagick
strip   |   \fCexiftool\fP   |   \fCapt install libimage-exiftool-perl\fP
PNG optimize   |   \fCoptipng\fP   |   \fCapt install optipng\fP
JPEG optimize   |   \fCjpegoptim\fP   |   \fCapt install jpegoptim\fP
WebP optimize   |   \fCcwebp\fP   |   \fCapt install webp\fP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
image info photo.jpg
image info photo.jpg --json
image resize photo.jpg --width 800 --out resized.jpg
image convert photo.png --format webp
image strip photo.jpg --out clean.jpg
image optimize photo.png
image thumb photo.jpg --size 200
.EE
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Flag   |   Meaning
\fC--width N\fP   |   Target width (pixels)
\fC--height N\fP   |   Target height (pixels)
\fC--percent N\fP   |   Resize by percentage
\fC--format FMT\fP   |   Target format (png, jpg, webp, gif)
\fC--quality N\fP   |   JPEG/WebP quality 1-100
\fC--size N\fP   |   Thumbnail max dimension
\fC--out FILE\fP   |   Output path
\fC--json\fP   |   Machine-readable output (info only)
